# Security Controls

## Security Control 1: Secure Remote Administrative Access

Explaination: Administrative access to internal systems should be restricted and hardened to prevent unauthorized remote access. Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) access should only be allowed through a VPN connection and restricted to
authorized administrative systems within a dedicated management subnet. Additionally, RDP must use Multi factor authentication (MFA). Firewall rules should disallow any RDP attempts from the internet.

These controls reduce the risk of attackers gaining administrative access through exposed RDP services or compromised credentials. Requiring a VPN and MFA also adds additional layers of protection that makes unauthorized access 
significantly more difficult.

